title: Is this Royal Club Just Empire in Disguise? | Empires of Dirt

media:group.media:title: Is this Royal Club Just Empire in Disguise? | Empires of Dirt
media:group.media:description:
After the death of Queen Elizabeth II, countries across the commonwealth are looking to remove the British monarch as their head of state or leave the Commonwealth entirely. 

As King Charles III takes the throne, can he hold his mother’s ‘favourite club’ together?

In the series, Royal Empires of Dirt, VICE World News host Zing Tsjeng looks into the shady royal history that rarely gets talked about.
